title: Version 128.6.0esr (64 bit) Update channel
creator: prdp141
content:
I was recently upgraded to Ver 128.6.0esr (64 bit) and I am not a fan of this version due to a number of concerns. Although a long term user of Thunderbird, no doubt my problem/s will be 'user error'.

I started off today hoping to put a stop to my New messages from being deleted automatically, even before I get to read them. (Seems to be a big concern and area of frustration with many MT users) Having just changed over from POP3 to IMAP (sick of losing msgs off the server) and following ALL instructions I seem to be going around and around without any +ve results or changes. Mind you this is the 3rd day now and cannot afford to be messing about as I have a business to operate.

First Problem - Re: stopping messages from auto deletion Action #1: I goto >Local folders> Disk Space and select ....'Don't delete any messages' Action #2: I goto >Sync & Storage>Message Sync>'Keep messages in all folders for this account on this computer' RESULT: No change. New messages go straight into deleted folder and are highlighted.

Second Problem - Stopping auto Compaction by Following instructions on Mozilla Help page Action #1: I goto >How Can I Configure Compact? Action #2: Select Preferences (formerly Options)>Network & Disk Space>Disk Space Action #3a: Cannot find Preferences Action #3b: or Options

Following instructions for Step #2 I open Application Menu as detailed and GUESS WHAT?.... 'Select Preferences (formerly Options)>Network & Disk Space>Disk Space' is nowhere to be seen.

I am wondering if anyone in the Thunderbird Tech Dev section has ever bothered a) Read and b) follow the instructions given to see if they actually display as described and then work.

Anyhow, can someone give me a straightforward reply and resolve to this matter as I am considering leaving MT and finding another agent that works as it is supposed to?

Thanking you in advance for any assistance.

Phil

title: Import from Outlook only bring across empty folders
creator: mozilla684
content:
When I ask Thunderbird to import from Outlook (under the tools menu) it only brings across empty folders.

For example, when it creates the “Outlook Import” set of folders in Thunderbird I get an empty “Outbox” folder. But it does not create an “Inbox” (that had 1 email in it, in my test case I was trying).

This is odd, because I’m sure I have seen this work correctly (importing all folders and emails) recently.

At first I thought it was something about this particular email account, so I tried another and got the same result. So I created a new user on the PC (Windows 11 with all the latest updates), set up an email account in Outlook there, did the import in Thunderbird and exactly the same happened, only the empty folders.

It does this with the main IMAP account I have set up in Outlook and also with a PST I opened in Outlook. It always runs without any errors, but only imports empty folders.

I’m using the latest build of Thunderbird (128.6.0esr (64-bit)). It’s also the latest version of Outlook Version 2501 (build 18429.20044).

What’s going on?

title: No connection to sent-Folder
creator: markussturm
content:
Hello.

I use Thunderbird 128.0esr on Win10.

Recently (maybe following the last update), I get the error (translated from German): "The message has been sent, but no copy has been saved to the Sent directory due to problems of access to network or files. You can try again or save the message to the local folder Sent....

Is there a solution?

Thanks a lot

Cheers

Markus
metadata: ;useragent:Mozilla/5.0 (Windows NT 10.0; Win64; x64; rv:134.0) Gecko/20100101 Firefox/134.0

title: Comcast Pop3 and STMP servers
creator: ndbrill
content:
Since an update 4-5 days ago, Comcast SMTP server does not accept login from Thunderbird. Comcast help page said it was updating and requires a more secure SSL security. Today the Pop3 server does not allow signin either.

How can I select a more secure encryption that will be compatible with comcast.

Thank you.

content: Hello everyone I would like you to help me if possible, I comment the problem I have with Thunderbird on Android and is as follows, as I can put a sound to send a message and if you can not, how you can see that the message has been sent correctly. I thank all the developers because you are doing a good job with Thunderbird for Android and people like me who have been waiting for years I think from my point of view that there are some things to improve to be almost perfect .... title: Matrix chat does not display any messages
creator: j-schneid
content: I have successfully signed into a Matrix chat and there was a list of messages I could read. But in most later Thunderbird sessions, the Window stays emtpy although in the bottom right corner of the screen popup windows with Matrix messages do appear. In the left pane the rooms I have entered should be displayed, but they are not. When I re-enter a room by hitting the button and re-typing the room's name, the list of joined chats, consisting of this one, appears in the left pane for the fraction of a second. I don't see any item in the config options for chat where I could have screwed something up.
metadata: ;useragent:Mozilla/5.0 (Windows NT 10.0; Win64; x64; rv:134.0) Gecko/20100101 Firefox/134.0

title: problem with opening image joined in a message
creator: melanie.dugas
content:
Hi, I'm not able to open jpg files which are joined in a message. When I want to, I can't find the default application Photos in the choice menu (see the images). I have installed the "visionneuse de photos windows" which replaces the default application Photos for windows 10. I think maybe it is the source of the problem, but I can't find any solution to open images whithout saving them in my computer. I don't understand why the "Photos" defaul application doesn't even appear in the choice, while it is still installed on my computer.

Is there anybody who can help me ? Thanks !
